title.rendered: Mumbai vs UP, India Women’s League 2023: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team on basis of probable XIs, recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Mumbai: Hayley Matthews, Yastika Bhatia (wk), Nat Sciver-Brunt, Harmanpreet Kaur (c), Amelia Kerr, Pooja Vastrakar, Issy Wong, Amanjot Kaur, Humaira Kazi, Jintimani Kalita, Saika Ishaque

UP: Shweta Sehrawat, Alyssa Healy (c & wk), Simran Shaikh, Tahlia McGrath, Kiran Navgire,  Deepti Sharma, Sophie Ecclestone, Anjali Sarvani, Parshavi Chopra, Soppadhandi Yashasri, Shabnim Ismail

Pitch Report

Venue: Dr DY Patil Sports Academy, Navi Mumbai

(Based on the last three games)

1st innings average score: 120

2nd innings average score: 177

Wickets per innings: 7

Type: Favours chasing

Wins

Batting 1st: —

Batting 2nd: 100%

Also Read:

Afghanistan vs Pakistan, 1st T20I Fantasy Tips

South Africa vs West Indies, 1st T20I: Fantasy Tips

Fantasy Tips of The Day 

Tahlia McGrath is the only player to slam four fifties in the tournament, while also generating a 30-run bonus in one of the other three matches.

Barring the last match, Harmanpreet Kaur had featured in the Best11 for four consecutive games. At the Dr DY Patil Sports Academy, she has accumulated 126 runs at 32.

At the same venue, Issy Wong has taken seven wickets, added 64 crucial runs down the order, and held onto two catches.

Yastika Bhatia has made an impact with bat and gloves in this competition. Besides collecting 189 runs, she has inflicted 11 dismissals.

Although Saika Ishaque has only one wicket to show for her efforts in the last four games, one cannot ignore the fact that she is the joint-leading wicket-taker (13), along with Amelia Kerr for Mumbai.

Amelia Kerr (61 runs and nine wickets) and Alyssa Healy (115 runs and four dismissals) have made it to the Best11 in four out of the last five games.

When these teams locked horns a week ago, Sophie Ecclestone (three wickets and 16 runs) and Deepti Sharma (two wickets, 13 runs and two run outs) were the captain and vice-captain of the Best11 respectively.

Shweta Sehrawat has managed only 33 runs in five innings in this edition.
